What you need to know:

Sofapaka coach Ken Odhiambo, who joined the club on January 1 from Bandari, also heaped praises on the  28-year-old, saying he has been playing him behind the lead striker because he is a clinical finisher."He is a good player who possess the ball and has the ability to shoot on target from far. While opponents concentrate on marking our strikers, Juma gets the opportunity to roam around and utilise he available opportunities that come our way to score goals," said Odhiambo.